Where to begin. I was attending an event and needed to get some doughnuts to take. I read good reviews on this bakery and it was convenient. So they close at 4:00 but...they were basically out of doughnuts at 2:30 (August 2, 2025). Very poor service planning.  Can’t be because the doughnuts were exceptional.  Meh.  The chairs were on the tables and another young lady was sweeping or mopping. As a business person, that is weird I thought. So that's that. Then I had the misfortune of speaking with a young lady, short, maybe Caucasion, dark hair about 28 who said she was the manager. I am not sure though as she was smirking when I asked if she was the manager. Yes, smirking. So, I did not have my glasses on as I had left them in my car. I started asking about pricing and trying to make a dozen of something with what was left. She was condescending, seemed annoyed at my questions for some reason and did not try to hide it. She kept saying...as it says on the menu...blah, blah blah with a TUDE. Like is this real...come on. Is it that hard to tell me prices??? This is about the POOR service at this store. I recommend Jelly Doughnuts or Sugar doughnuts. Not close but great everything at those similar spots according to friends.
OMG the donuts!

I stopped by on my way back to Atlanta, and I'm soooooooo glad I did. I love the fact that I can choose my own filling, because that vanilla buttercream is the TRUTH. And I waited a day to eat the apple fritter, and it still smelled and tasted like they just made it. Literally melted in my mouth. I just wish it had more apples!

I'll definitely be back next time I'm in town.

Very delicious donuts.  Absolutely the best donuts I have found in the area since moving here back in 2016.

My family and I stopped in just before our visit to the motor speedway and we are so glad we did! They had a good variety of donuts, even after the morning rush (which a customer told us we arrived just after haha). The filled donuts are filled with your choice of filling right when you order it! We got a maple eclair with vanilla buttercream, strawberry filled with vanilla buttercream, chocolate filled with raspberry, another amazing donut i am forgetting but it was also raspberry filled, and an apple fritter. My dad was so happy with the apple fritter as it had pieces of apple all throughout which were delicious. The donuts are very good!! Be aware they are also very sweet though. They are also massive!! More than palm sized, so one donut is plenty if you are not a sugar addict. I am a sugar addict and I made it through my eclair and half of my strawberry donut before i had to cut my losses and get a to go bag. I also ordered a Vietnamese iced coffee. It was a little bitter for my taste, so I asked the server if she would be able to help and she let me add some cane sugar syrup to it to brighten the flavor which made a huge difference! I really appreciate her going out of her way to help me like that. Overall the staff are wonderful and the donuts are fantastic! I hope to visit again next time I am in Charlotte

Every Sunday morning, I have the same routine. I wake up before my family, throw some clothes on, and sneak out into the early morning, as the sun starts to slowly peek over the horizon. The roads are empty, and I enjoy my favorite music quietly playing over the speakers and the rumbling of the road beneath me. After about 10 minutes, I arrive at this unassuming building - just another spot in a small strip mall. Then, I walk in - bright colors, happy signage, and the lovely, sweet smell of fresh baked goods overtake my senses. That familiar sugary, doughy scent first thing in the morning evokes such a feeling of warmth and comfort - I feel the same way I did as a little girl, when I woke up at my grandma’s house to a fresh breakfast waiting for me on the table. I pick out a delicious assortment of donuts, helped by the friendly team behind the counter. I leave with a huge smile and eagerly drive home to bring the treats to my family. By the time I get home, the kids are awake, and seeing the joy on their faces gives a feeling I wish I could bottle up and keep with me forever. We each pick out our favorite donut, sit together, laugh, and enjoy some quality family time. This is one of my favorite parts of the week. I truly believe the love put into these donuts materializes in how delicious, fluffy, and flavorful they are. They are simply perfection. The texture, the size, the toppings - PERFECT. I literally dream about these donuts and look forward to every weekend when we have them. I cannot recommend OMG enough- y’all are awesome! Thanks for being apart of so many of our family memories- and even more for years to come.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Our goal is to not have too much left over at the end of the day because we make our donuts the same day and we never sale day old donuts. We do not charge $2.35 for a glazed donut, in fact, it is $1.35. The chocolate donuts are $1.65. We are more than happy to take preorders so that you are sure to get the flavors you like.

Where to begin. I was attending an event and needed to get some doughnuts to take. I read good reviews on this bakery and it was convenient. So they close at 4:00 but...they were basically out of doughnuts at 2:30 (August 2, 2025). Very poor service planning.  Can’t be because the doughnuts were exceptional.  Meh.  The chairs were on the tables and another young lady was sweeping or mopping. As a business person, that is weird I thought. So that's that. Then I had the misfortune of speaking with a young lady, short, maybe Caucasion, dark hair about 28 who said she was the manager. I am not sure though as she was smirking when I asked if she was the manager. Yes, smirking. So, I did not have my glasses on as I had left them in my car. I started asking about pricing and trying to make a dozen of something with what was left. She was condescending, seemed annoyed at my questions for some reason and did not try to hide it. She kept saying...as it says on the menu...blah, blah blah with a TUDE. Like is this real...come on. Is it that hard to tell me prices??? This is about the POOR service at this store. I recommend Jelly Doughnuts or Sugar doughnuts. Not close but great everything at those similar spots according to friends.

My family and I stopped in just before our visit to the motor speedway and we are so glad we did! They had a good variety of donuts, even after the morning rush (which a customer told us we arrived just after haha). The filled donuts are filled with your choice of filling right when you order it! We got a maple eclair with vanilla buttercream, strawberry filled with vanilla buttercream, chocolate filled with raspberry, another amazing donut i am forgetting but it was also raspberry filled, and an apple fritter. My dad was so happy with the apple fritter as it had pieces of apple all throughout which were delicious. The donuts are very good!! Be aware they are also very sweet though. They are also massive!! More than palm sized, so one donut is plenty if you are not a sugar addict. I am a sugar addict and I made it through my eclair and half of my strawberry donut before i had to cut my losses and get a to go bag. I also ordered a Vietnamese iced coffee. reviews_data.review_text: I love this place.  The donuts are amazing. My favorite place for a sweet treat.  I haven't had a donut I didn't like there yet,  and I have tried at least half the menu at this point.

I've tried many many donuts. OMG is my top favorite. Before I moved to NC, I'd come visit my sister for the weekend, and I'd beg her to take me. No other donuts compare in my mind. I like the non-cakey donuts - so OMG donuts are my favorite.

Best donut place, hands-down. We ordered several donuts for my daughter’s birthday party and hung them on a donut rack. Everyone was obsessed. I go here once a week. The strawberry shortcake is my absolute favorite, followed by the toasted caramel Samoa. My mother-in-law is coming into town for the holidays and I had already asked the staff if they plan to be open Christmas Eve or the day before, so I can rack up on donuts go here you will not be disappointed

UPDATE 12/3/23:
They are now serving espresso drinks! I had to update my review because I had the best oat milk latte from them this morning! It tasted delicious and the espresso was so well done! Highly recommend! OMG can do no wrong!

Every Sunday morning, I have the same routine. I wake up before my family, throw some clothes on, and sneak out into the early morning, as the sun starts to slowly peek over the horizon. The roads are empty, and I enjoy my favorite music quietly playing over the speakers and the rumbling of the road beneath me. After about 10 minutes, I arrive at this unassuming building - just another spot in a small strip mall. Then, I walk in - bright colors, happy signage, and the lovely, sweet smell of fresh baked goods overtake my senses. That familiar sugary, doughy scent first thing in the morning evokes such a feeling of warmth and comfort - I feel the same way I did as a little girl, when I woke up at my grandma’s house to a fresh breakfast waiting for me on the table. I pick out a delicious assortment of donuts, helped by the friendly team behind the counter. I leave with a huge smile and eagerly drive home to bring the treats to my family. By the time I get home, the kids are awake, and seeing the joy on their faces gives a feeling I wish I could bottle up and keep with me forever. We each pick out our favorite donut, sit together, laugh, and enjoy some quality family time. This is one of my favorite parts of the week. I truly believe the love put into these donuts materializes in how delicious, fluffy, and flavorful they are. They are simply perfection. The texture, the size, the toppings - PERFECT. I literally dream about these donuts and look forward to every weekend when we have them. I cannot recommend OMG enough- y’all are awesome! Thanks for being apart of so many of our family memories- and even more for years to come.
Donuts are awesome, staff is friendly. Love this place

y'all-  YOU HAVE to go here! We were visiting from out of town and got a dozen mixed to go! These were the tastiest, fluffiest, most delicious doughnuts I have ever had! Both of my toddlers ate the entire doughnut- not just the toppings. These make another popular doughnut chain look like they are the wish version and OMG is the delicious OG. 10/10 They even asked if we had any allergy restrictions- we do not but I appreciate the ask.

Still, the place to go for scrumptious, fresh donuts! Their apple fritters are the best! Eat in or take out....either way is a win-win.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Our goal is to not have too much left over at the end of the day because we make our donuts the same day and we never sale day old donuts. We do not charge $2.35 for a glazed donut, in fact, it is $1.35. The chocolate donuts are $1.65. We are more than happy to take preorders so that you are sure to get the flavors you like.

Third, the staff are awesome. They were super friendly and even helped take a family picture of us behind their donut board.
I highly recommend this place.
